Gumperz adopts a synchronic, interactionist approach which
focuses on well-defined speech communities in the following ways:

--Sociolinguistics  is defined as language usage that reflects
    societal norms.                                 <socgum1.11>

--Social Context is integral to theorizing.          <socgum1.12>

--The object of study is verbal interaction.         <socgum1.13>

--the efficacy of historical approaches is questionable,
therefore synchronic studies are required            <socgum1.14>

--The speech community is a "socially defined universe"
